China Stocks: Huaxin Cement, Qingdao Haier, Shanghai Electric

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-28T07:41:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/china-stocks-huaxin-cement-qingdao-haier-shanghai-electric.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3 p.m. close.  The  Shanghai  Composite Index added 26.5 points, or 0.9
percent to 2,905.05. The  CSI 300 Index  gained 1.3 percent to
3,239.56.  Cement makers and machinery makers: Huaxin Cement Co.
(600801 CH) rose 3 percent to 40.19 yuan, the highest close
since Jan. 15, 2008. Anhui Conch Cement Co. (6005858 CH) climbed
1 percent to 34.61 yuan, the highest since Feb. 20, 2008. Sany
Heavy Industry Co. (600031 CH) surged 8.5 percent to a record
25.20 yuan. China plans to build 36 million affordable homes in
the next five years, Premier  Wen Jiabao  said in an online
interview yesterday.  Home appliance makers: Qingdao Haier Co. (600690 CH) jumped
6.3 percent to 30.85 yuan, the highest since its listing in Nov.
1993.  Gree Electric Appliances Inc . (000651 CH) increased 5.4
percent to 21.21 yuan, the highest since its listing in November
1996. GF Securities Co. said higher product prices will boost
earnings for home appliance makers, making them defensive
against the government’s inflation control measures.  Shanghai Electric Power Co. (600021 CH) lost 3.5 percent to
4.70 yuan, the biggest decline since Nov. 12. The company said
it canceled a refinancing plan. The company said it won’t
consider any major asset restructuring within the next three
months, according to a statement to the Shanghai exchange.    TCL Corp . (000100 CH) surged 10 percent to 4.82 yuan, its
highest close since April 26. The Chinese television maker said
it plans to give investors one bonus share for each share held.  -- Irene Shen, Winnie Zhu. Editors: Richard Frost, Allen Wan  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
